sub_title: Teacher of English (ESL) at Stedelijk Gymnasium Leiden
summary:
About me...

My current mission is to create inclusive classrooms, using globally relevant subject matters and modern approaches to language comprehension. I am creative, good at creating and processing promotional and scaffolding materials and I possess in-depth knowledge of graphical tools. I grew up in both England and the Netherlands and I am completely native in both Dutch and English. I have translated official websites and manuals for companies (such as Aquacrafts) during my BA, but U quickly found out that my passion is in the field of literature, writing and education. My writing skills include academic writing and journalism, and my academic achievements include a certificate in graphic design, as well as a full minor degree in book studies. My personal interests include travel, language and culture and I have a great love for art and music.

 I am a first-degree teacher of English in higher secondary education, with a supplementary certificate in international and bilingual education (ICLON / World Teachers Programme). I did my internship at the Rotterdam International Secondary School. I am currently employed at the Stedelijk Gymnasium in Leiden as an English teacher.

The World Teachers Programme is a specialist programme within the ICLON post-master teachers' degree, and is provided by Leiden University for a selected amount of student teachers each year. The programme is aimed at training teachers (in English) to gain experience beyond the Dutch schooling system. The World Teachers Programme is also aimed at creating academic, empathetic and culturally aware teachers that wish to contribute to the development of bright and responsible adolescents.

Background Education:
I finished my educational MA in first degree teaching in 2021. Before that, I graduated in Literary Studies at Leiden University in 2019, with cum laude honours (with a grade average of 8,0).
My MA thesis was called "Identity Politics and The Handmaid's Tale" and was awarded an 8,2.  finished my BA in English Language and Culture in 2017 (at Leiden University).

Some of my previous work experiences include: customer service representative at Websend, information and promotion for beginning students at the University of Leiden, creating promotional material and texts and tracking websites and social media for different (student) associations and organisations such as OJV de Koornbeurs in Delft, and the Rotterdam International School.
